scholarship /ˈskɒləʃɪp/

(scholarships) 

1. N-COUNT If you get a scholarship to a school or university, your studies are paid for by the school or university or by some other organization. 奖学金 

例： He got a scholarship to the Pratt Institute of Art. 他得到了一笔普拉特艺术学院的奖学金。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Scholarship is serious academic study and the knowledge that is obtained from it. 学术研究; 学问成就 

例： I want to take advantage of your lifetime of scholarship. 我想从您一生的学术成就中获益。

</div>

